name: First Dates Australia
overview: When the First Dates restaurant sets the table, hopeful singles from across the country will have a chance of meeting their dream partner. They’ve turned their backs on online dating in the hope of meeting someone special face-to-face, and they’ll meet their potential love match for the very first time in the restaurant.

production_companies.name: Warner Bros. International Television Production Australia

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: There's someone out there for everyone, and when the first dates restaurant sets the table, singles from across the country will have a chance of meeting their dream partner.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: They've come from right across the country to face the most intense night of their lives. On this episode, a dater returns. Will she find true love?

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: A pretty PA is back to give love another chance and an Aussie Magic Mike leaves a lasting impression on his date.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Tonight, a real-life Magic Mike looks for love, and two twins take to the First Dates restaurant. Another dater returns, but can she get past her date's love of cats and find love?

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Tonight, a man with a love of Home And Away meets his match in an aspiring journalist. Also, a single mother goes on her first date in many years and a young teen has her first date ever.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Tonight, a travelling circus performer, stuntman and racehorse trainer go in search of love. Plus, a girl who followed the yellow brick road to be here - will she find Mr Right in Oz?

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Tonight, Anthony scores a second First Date. Will the luck of the Irish be on his side? And will it be destiny when a celebrity psychic medium meets an intuitive healer?

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: In the series final of First Dates, will a magician cast a spell on his date and will a music student hit the right notes during her romantic meal?

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: There's someone out there for everyone, and when the first dates restaurant sets the table, hopeful singles from across the country will have a chance of meeting their dream partner.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: A dater returns for a second chance at love. Will she finally meet the man of her dreams? Also, an executive assistant is ready to start dating again after a devastating breakup.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: A Beyonce single lady is looking for someone to put a ring on it. A memorable Romeo is back for a second chance at love. A makeup artist whose love life is in desperate need of a makeover.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: An Instagram queen goes looking for her king. A fly-in, fly-out coal mine worker's been struggling to ignite her love life. Will tonight be a blast for her? An unlucky in love dater is back.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: A nursing student hopes to light a spark with an electrician, a banker is keen to invest a little more in his love life with a doctor, and a straight-talking bar manager searches for the one.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Can bodybuilder Lauren get gym junkie Luke's heart rate up? A single mum's idea of the perfect man is Dwayne 'The Rock' Johnson. Will her date Dwayne live up to her expectations?

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: In this episode, serial dater Stephanie has a secret crush on Malcom Turnbull. Also, Sanjay considers himself a catch, and rates himself a 9.5 out of 10.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Meet Anna, a lady in the kitchen and a freak in the bedroom, and Tony, who likens women to crocodiles as they both want to kill you at some stage.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: Two work colleagues find themselves on a blind date together, and a young man who has never had a boyfriend hopes to meet someone he can introduce to his parents.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: In this episode, a fashionista tries to find love in person after trying every online dating site. Mick returns for a second shot at love, this time with Chelsea, who has never been on a date before.

episodes.name: Episode 11
episodes.overview: A country boy comes to the city in search of love; An enthusiastic DJ hopes to finally graduate from the friend zone; and a first-time blind dater orders tequila shots to get the party started.

episodes.name: Episode 12
episodes.overview: A young professional is looking for someone to build an empire with; a man is wondering if it's possible to find the 'best' girlfriend; and a self-proclaimed Greek god looks to settle down.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Jana, a lingerie designer, is looking to fufill her dream of being carried into the sunset; Andrew hopes to woo a date with his unique dancing abilities and begin his first serious relationship.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Skipping teacher Emma meets teacher and personal trainer Kane; romantic Alistair is hoping for someone down to earth; pet photographer Adam looks for someone like-minded.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Self-confessed joker Josh searches for his perfect match. Skipping teacher Emma is back for round two. Hairdresser Bronte looks for a man who is a cut above the rest.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: In an Australian first, the red carpet is rolled out for a Logie award-winning TV legend. A new dater has a laugh you'll never forget, and another might just be Australia's worst eater.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: One lucky dater goes on a blind date with Geordie Shore star, James Tindale. Two daters prove that age is just a number. We encounter Australia’s raunchiest dater.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: One of Australia’s top international models, Simone Holtznagel, is looking for a tall man to meet her strict height requirements. At 6 foot 8, will Peter prove to be a slam dunk for Simone?

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Hoping to find someone to get their hearts racing are these two V8 loving bogans, Ebony and Nick. Also, a brother and sister are duo both searching for the perfect man (not the same one!)

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: A dater brings her dad along for her date. Also, aspiring white Kiwi rapper Tyler meets a saccharine Princess who can burp the alphabet

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Shadi has returned to the restaurant for the fourth time! But he's back a different man. He's lost a lot of weight, he's found faith and his chastity belt is now back tightly in place.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: First up tonight is celebrity Ajay Rochester, bringing big energy! She instantly hits it off with her date, truckie Matt. Young singletons Claudia and Jack bring the sizzle in this episode

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Vivacious Danielle is looking for a good guy who can ultimately just “get it up”. Brandon hopes his Dad jokes and "Red Jesus" beard can win over his date, Casey.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: To start this evening off with a bang, is long-legged beauty, Britney. Pairing her with down-to-earth James, she is absolutely smitten by him

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: It’s a First Dates first, with twin sisters, Isabella and Adelaide, teaming up on a double date. English Gentleman Will is looking to find someone who can make him laugh. Cue hot-blooded Siria.

episodes.name: Episode 11
episodes.overview: She’s a 54-year-old looking for another shot at love, but can Taryn look past reality star Nasser’s onscreen MAFS marriage and find a connection?

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: First Dates Australia is the heart-warming, heart-breaking and occasionally heart-stopping fly-on-the-wall dating series, that takes viewers inside the intimate world of genuine first dates.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Come along for the ride as singles settle in for genuine blind dates. Everyone can relate to the promise of potential love when it goes well and the hilariously awkward moments if it crashes and burns
